# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>
#
# 🎯 ADHD-Friendly Commit Guide:
# 
# Types (pick one):
#   feat: ✨ New feature
#   fix: 🐛 Bug fix  
#   docs: 📝 Documentation
#   style: 💄 Code style/format
#   refactor: ♻️ Code refactoring
#   perf: ⚡ Performance improvement
#   test: 🧪 Add/update tests
#   build: 🏗️ Build system
#   ci: 👷 CI/CD changes
#   chore: 🧹 Maintenance
#   revert: ⏪ Revert commit
#   wip: 🚧 Work in progress
#
# Scope (optional): api, web, utils, server, etc.
# Subject: Brief description (50 chars max, no period)
# Body: Detailed explanation (wrap at 72 chars)
# Footer: Breaking changes, closes issues
#
# Examples:
#   feat(api): add user authentication endpoint
#   fix(web): resolve navigation mobile bug
#   docs: update installation instructions
#   wip: experimenting with new layout
#
# 💡 Quick commits: Use `pnpm commit` for interactive prompts
# 🚀 Bypass hooks: Use `HUSKY=0 git commit` in emergencies
# 📦 Changesets: Run `pnpm changeset` for version changes